column11: Products and features are relevant to what customer wants (8)
column18: Feedback

The submission demonstrates strong organization and relevant content but has formatting inconsistencies, minor grammar issues, and lacks a recording. Next steps and remaining questions are well-articulated.
The submission demonstrates strong organization, relevant competitor analysis, and clear next steps, but could improve by balancing open/closed questions and providing a more detailed transcript.
Strong organization and clear next steps, but needs improvement in transcript detail and table readability. Relevant product analysis and well-defined roles enhance submission quality.

Strengths include relevant product research and clear next-step questions. Weaknesses include disorganized structure, redundancy in the table, and insufficient depth in summarizing critical interview points.
Strong structure, relevant research, and clear next steps, but roles could be more defined and unresolved questions need addressing.
The submission demonstrates strong structure, relevant features, and effective interview techniques, but could improve in detailing unresolved questions and refining next steps for clarity.

Submission demonstrates strong structure and role clarity but needs improvement in transcript depth and grammar. Relevant questions and clear next steps are strengths, while analysis tables and learning points could be more detailed.
The submission demonstrates strong alignment with customer requirements and structured planning, but lacks clarity in transcripts, visual tables, and recording documentation.
Strong analysis of competitors and clear project structure, but transcript completeness and depth in learning points need improvement. Next steps are well-defined and actionable.
Strong research analysis, clear task breakdown, and relevant questions. Missing recording documentation and minor grammar issues lower some scores.
Strong in summarizing critical points, outlining next steps, and aligning features with customer needs. Minor weaknesses in transcript detail and table readability.
Strong structure, role clarity, and actionable next steps, but grammar issues and incomplete transcript details weaken submission. Excellent market analysis and relevant questions.
Strong structure, clear roles, and relevant features align with customer needs. Missing recording and slightly vague remaining questions lower some scores.
Submission demonstrates clear role allocation and structured questions but lacks depth in summarizing critical points, has grammatical errors, and omits recording documentation.
Submission shows organized research and relevant product alignment but lacks clarity in learning points, unresolved questions, and structural polish in formatting/transcripts.

The submission demonstrates clear role distribution and relevant product analysis but lacks depth in transcript details, grammatical polish, and explicit recording confirmation. Next steps and unresolved questions need refinement.
Strengths include clear roles, relevant features, and actionable next steps. Weaknesses include minor structural disorganization, lack of a full transcript, and cramped table formatting.
Strong organization and relevant questions address customer needs effectively. Areas for improvement include transcript detail and deeper alignment of features with customer priorities.
Strong research, next steps, and question clarity, but lacks role assignments and has minor structural/grammatical issues. Transcript link appears to reference a recording, not a written summary.

Submission covers key aspects but lacks depth in analysis, clarity in role assignments, and explicit articulation of remaining questions. Strengths include structured interview scripts and transcript summaries; weaknesses include grammatical errors and incomplete product relevance analysis.

The submission covers required elements but lacks depth in analysis, clarity in organization, and attention to detail. Strengths include relevant product comparisons and user stories; weaknesses include unclear structure, grammatical errors, and incomplete next steps.
Strong structure and clear learning points, but roles could be more specific and transcript/table readability improved. Relevant questions and actionable next steps demonstrate good planning.
The submission demonstrates strong organization, relevant feature alignment, and actionable next steps. Minor weaknesses include limited transcript detail and slightly underdeveloped learning points.

The submission demonstrates clear role assignments and relevant feature analysis but lacks depth in grammar, structure, and recording documentation. Strengths include a well-organized table and focused questions; weaknesses include incomplete learning points and transcript detail.

The submission demonstrates adequate structure and relevance but lacks depth in role clarity, question design, and actionable next steps. Strengths include a clear analysis table and functional alignment with customer needs.
The submission demonstrates strong alignment with customer needs and clear next steps, but lacks structured presentation of research and some interview documentation details.

The submission demonstrates strong organization, relevant questioning, and clear next steps. Areas for improvement include enhancing transcript clarity and ensuring visual elements (tables/figures) are fully accessible and legible.

The submission demonstrates strong organization and role clarity but lacks depth in competitor analysis, transcript quality, and addressing unresolved questions. Grammar and table readability need improvement, while next steps and learning points are adequately outlined.
Strong structure and relevant analysis, but transcript depth and table readability could improve. Clear next steps and effective summarization of critical interview points.
Submission is well-organized with thorough analysis and clear next steps, but minor structural inconsistencies and some ambiguity in remaining questions slightly limit clarity.

The submission demonstrates strong role allocation and relevant questioning but lacks clarity in transcript organization and fails to address recording. Next steps are outlined but require more specificity.
The submission demonstrates strong organization and relevant analysis but has minor issues in grammar, formatting clarity, and incomplete recording documentation.

The submission is well-structured with relevant questions and clear next steps, but lacks depth in transcript details and table readability. Roles and product relevance could be more precisely aligned with customer needs.

The submission demonstrates strong alignment with client requirements and clear role definitions, but lacks a detailed transcript, explicit unresolved questions, and recording documentation. Structural clarity and table formatting could be improved.
The submission is well-structured with clear roles and relevant research, but lacks detail in the transcript and analysis table. Next steps and remaining questions are thoughtfully addressed.
The submission demonstrates strong organization, role clarity, and relevant next steps, but lacks detailed transcripts, visual tables, and minor grammatical polish.
Submission demonstrates strong organization, relevant feature analysis, and actionable next steps, but lacks clarity in question structuring and transcript documentation.

The submission demonstrates strong relevance to customer goals and structured questioning, but lacks clarity in role definitions and transcript depth. Grammar errors and repetitive content slightly weaken presentation.
Strengths include clear role assignments and structured questions. Weaknesses include incomplete transcript clarity and unresolved questions needing refinement.

The submission demonstrates strong alignment with customer goals and clear next steps, but lacks refinement in table readability and explicit role contributions. Some criteria (e.g., transcript depth) could benefit from more detail.

The submission demonstrates strong structure, relevant product analysis, and clear role definitions. Areas for improvement include grammar refinement, deeper elaboration on next steps, and enhanced table readability.
Submission demonstrates clear role distribution and relevant product analysis but lacks depth in planning specifics, detailed learning insights, and structured question formulation.
Strong role definition and relevant questions, but needs improvement in grammar and table readability. Next steps are practical but could benefit from more specificity.

Submission demonstrates solid structure and planning but lacks depth in product relevance analysis and transcript clarity. Strengths include clear role distribution and next steps; weaknesses include minor grammatical issues and table readability.

Submission is well-structured with clear roles, relevant questions, and actionable next steps. Weaknesses include minor grammar issues, sparse research table formatting, and limited depth in summarizing interview critical points.

The submission demonstrates structured organization and relevant questioning but lacks depth in transcript detail and product relevance analysis. Next steps are clearly outlined, though some sections need improved clarity and conciseness.
The submission demonstrates strong organization, relevant research, and actionable next steps, but lacks a recording and deeper analysis in summarizing critical points and product relevance.
Strong structure, clear next steps, and thorough research. Minor deductions for role clarity and grammar, but overall well-organized and aligned with customer goals.
Strengths include clear role assignments and structured questions. Weaknesses include inconsistent grammar, unclear tables, and insufficiently detailed transcript summaries.

Submission is well-structured with clear roles and relevant questions, but lacks depth in transcript clarity, unresolved questions, and detailed next steps. Core features align with client needs, but some criteria (e.g., table readability) remain uncertain due to placeholder links.

The submission demonstrates organized research and relevant competitor analysis but lacks depth in summarizing critical insights and structuring questions effectively. Clear next steps and unresolved questions are well-documented.
The submission is well-structured with clear roles and relevant analysis, but grammar issues and minor gaps in question balance and transcript detail slightly reduce clarity.
Evaluation failed

The submission is well-structured with clear role distribution and relevant product analysis. However, it lacks a detailed transcript and recording documentation, and some sections require deeper elaboration.

The submission demonstrates strong organization and role clarity but lacks depth in analyzing existing solutions and addressing remaining questions. Grammar issues and table readability slightly weaken an otherwise thorough analysis.

Submission demonstrates strong structure, relevant questions, and competitive analysis. Weaknesses include incomplete transcript details and vague next steps. Legal considerations and scalability could be better addressed.

The submission demonstrates clear structure and relevant analysis but lacks detail in transcripts and visual readability of tables. Strengths include role clarity and competitor analysis; weaknesses include minor grammatical issues and incomplete design specifications.
